comment_data.body: This doesn't actually seem to be the case looking in more detail (except that the builtin memoryview getbuffer protocol is pretty optimized because it's mostly just copying). I suspect the optimization is mainly just in being able to skip creating the Cython memoryview much of the time

commit.message:
Optimize dispatch for fused memoryview types

By converting them to a memoryview once, checking some of the
details of that, and then using that to initialize the
Cython memoryview.

Also closes #3798 as an implementation detail.

I measure something like ~7% speedup on a small toy example
that selects between 3 types of memoryviews

Work around PyPy2 issue

I wasn't able to diagnose what's going on, but it doesn't
work if you go via an intermediate Python memoryview

Simplify workaround

Doesn't need special utility code
Undo change accidently copied into modulesetupcode
